# Own Microstock

Own Microstock is a separate local product/scaffold area for self-hosted or
device-owned microstock workflows. Keep it separate from the live Qwertystock
sales website and from shared domain automation.

- Canonical local scaffold path: `R:\M_plus_front\qwertystock-own-microstock`.
- Personal Codex skill path: `C:\Users\escho\.codex\skills\own-microstock`.
- Rules/docs may live in this repo under `.cursor/rules` or `docs` when they
  describe Qwertystock-adjacent boundaries.
- The canonical development memory for this product is
  `R:\M_plus_front\qwertystock-own-microstock\documentation\skill.md`. Update it
  with version, current stage, decisions, and TODO whenever Own Microstock flow,
  domain quoting, provisioning, tenant SEO, or deployment behavior changes.
- Do not implement Own Microstock features inside `R:\M_plus_front\qwertystock`
  unless the user explicitly asks for integration.
- Do not touch `R:\M_plus_front\qwertystock_domain_api` for Own Microstock work
  unless the user explicitly asks for domain/API integration.
- Do not include secrets, credentialized remotes, private keys, tokens, cookies,
  production env contents, or customer data in rules, skills, docs, or scaffold
  files.
- When the user explicitly asks for product integration, keep the runtime split:
  Qwertystock sells and manages the tenant, Way/domain-api owns registrar/DNS
  safety, and `qwertystock-own-microstock` owns tenant storefront code.

## Post-Purchase Lifecycle

After a paid Own Microstock invoice, the system must progress through explicit,
idempotent steps:

1. `domain_purchase_success`
2. `dns_configured`
3. `site_deployed`
4. `ssl_ready`
5. `robots_txt_generated`
6. `sitemap_generated`
7. `indexnow_key_generated`
8. `indexnow_key_file_deployed`
9. `search_engines_submit_job_created`
10. `active`

Provisioning must be asynchronous and retryable. Payment finalization must not
depend on long DNS, SSL, Search Console, Bing, Yandex, or IndexNow calls.
Each step must be safe to rerun without double domain registration, duplicate
DNS writes, duplicate deploys, or repeated search-engine spam.

Do not mark a tenant as `active` until public checks pass for the tenant domain:
`/`, `/robots.txt`, `/sitemap.xml`, and `/{indexnow_key}.txt`. These checks are
required because domain purchase alone does not prove that the tenant storefront
is actually reachable.

## Tenant SEO

Every tenant domain must expose these public routes at minimum:

- `/`
- `/about`
- `/license`
- `/contact`
- `/robots.txt`
- `/sitemap.xml`
- `/{indexnow_key}.txt`
- `/category/...`
- `/model/...`

Each tenant gets its own IndexNow key and root key file. Bing/Yandex submission
uses IndexNow and Webmaster APIs where credentials are configured. Google uses
Search Console API, sitemap submission, DNS/site verification when available,
and high-quality crawlable links from Qwertystock.

Tenant social previews are part of SEO. Every active tenant must provide
canonical Open Graph/Twitter metadata for Telegram and other social unfurlers:
`og:title`, `og:description`, `og:url`, `og:image`, `twitter:image`, and
`og:video` when a suitable tenant video preview exists. Preview media must come
from the tenant author's own catalog, preferring the strongest/trending video
poster, then photo, then vector/illustration preview. Never use the old global
Qwertystock logo or an empty preview for tenant domains.

Default tenant social description should be English and buyer-facing:
"Buy stock content directly from the author at a fair price. Royalty-free
licenses for media products are available on this site." Public tenant pages
must not mention internal implementation details, providers, workers, servers,
or registry APIs.

## Anti-Clone Rule

Own Microstock sites must use a shared engine, not shared output. Do not publish
full clones of Qwertystock or of other tenant sites.

- Tenant catalog scope is only that author/brand's visible sellable files or an
  explicitly curated owned catalog.
- Tenant home/about/category/model pages must have unique brand text, title,
  description, hero/featured media, category order, and theme/layout variant.
- Tenant sitemaps must contain only tenant URLs, never the full Qwertystock
  catalog.
- Tenant canonicals must point to the tenant domain, not `qwertystock.com`.
- Qwertystock may link to each tenant through a curated `/brands/...` page, and
  the tenant may link back to the Qwertystock profile. Do not build a large
  mutual-link grid between tenant domains.
